  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental factors gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: All validation experiments were conducted under controlled laboratory conditions (22°C, atmospheric pressure, no EM interference characterization). The actual clinical deployment environment involves operating-room temperature fluctuations (18–26°C), variable ambient pressure at altitude, and electromagnetic interference from adjacent surgical equipment. No environmental-sensitivity study has been performed, and the operating envelope does not bound these parameters.",
