      "name": "Lab flow-bench hemolysis measurement — 22°C, atmospheric pressure",
      "description": "Experimental hemolysis index measurements collected on the FDA generic centrifugal pump test rig at 22°C ambient temperature and standard atmospheric pressure (101.325 kPa). Five flow-speed operating points tested. No electromagnetic shielding assessment performed. No altitude or pressure-variation sweep conducted. CFD predictions of normalized index of hemolysis (nIH) compared against measured values; all five operating points met RH < 1 criterion. Environmental conditions during testing were not varied and no sensitivity study linking environmental parameter drift to hemolysis prediction accuracy was performed."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error study",
