    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors not assessed are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. CFD predictions of nIH are within 13% of laboratory measurements across all five operating points, and RH < 1 is satisfied. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device regulatory submission. The assessment team notes that all validation evidence was collected under controlled laboratory conditions (22°C, atmospheric pressure) and that the operating-room deployment environment (temperature 18–26°C, altitude-dependent pressure, EM interference from surgical equipment) has not been characterized or bounded in the validation evidence base. This environmental characterization gap is acknowledged but was not adjudicated as a barrier to acceptance at MRL 2 given the medium model influence designation.",
